Enum Class UIState

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<UIState>
com.comp2042.model.UIState
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<UIState>, Constable
public enum UIState extends Enum<UIState>
Enum representing the different UI states and screens in the Tetris application. This enum is used to manage the visibility of different menus and game screens, ensuring only the appropriate UI elements are shown at any given time.

UI States:

  • HOME - Main menu screen
  • HOW_TO_PLAY - Instructions and tutorial screen
  • THEMES - Theme selection menu
  • GAME - Active gameplay screen
  • PAUSED - Paused game overlay
  • GAME_OVER - Game over screen with final score
  • LEADERBOARD - High scores display
